# TurboQuant KV-cache quant types for llama.cpp
#
# Adds two KV-cache quantization types from TurboQuant (arXiv:2504.19874):
#
#   - GGML_TYPE_TQ_MSE_4  (Algorithm 1): per-head random rotation Pi +
#     Lloyd-Max codebook on the rotated coordinates. 4 bits per element +
#     fp16 norm scale. ~4.125 bpv. Block size 128 (head dim).
#
#   - GGML_TYPE_TQ_PROD_4 (Algorithm 2): MSE-4 stage (above) + 1-bit JL
#     sign sketch of the per-block residual + fp16 residual scale gamma.
#     The sketch is performed in the rotated basis (a fresh iid Gaussian
#     matrix M plays the role of S * Pi^T from the prototype's unit-space
#     sketch). 5.25 bpv. Provides an unbiased inner-product estimator,
#     unlike the pure MSE variant.
#
# Both exposed via --cache-type-k tq_mse_4 / tq_prod_4. Both have CPU and
# CUDA paths; attention runs through the cuBLAS F32 fallback in both cases
# (no fused vec-dot or flash-attn template instances yet).
#
# Base commit (upstream ggml-org/llama.cpp):
#   cf8b0dbda server : remove /api endpoints (#22165)
#
# Apply with:
#   cd llama.cpp
#   git apply ../patches/turboquant-llama.cpp.patch
#
# Build & test (CPU):
#   cmake -B build -DGGML_CUDA=OFF
#   cmake --build build -j
#   ./build/bin/test-turboquant         # MSE-4 round trip + vec_dot
#   ./build/bin/test-turboquant-prod    # Prod-4 round trip + vec_dot
#   ./build/bin/llama-completion -m model.gguf -p "..." \
#       --cache-type-k tq_mse_4 --jinja
#   ./build/bin/llama-completion -m model.gguf -p "..." \
#       --cache-type-k tq_prod_4 --jinja
#
# Build & test (CUDA):
#   scripts/test-cuda-turboquant.sh                   # all four tests
#   scripts/test-cuda-turboquant.sh -m model.gguf     # + end-to-end gen
#
